snippet.title: A basic model for practice of intracranial microsurgery
snippet.description:
* A basic model for practice of intracranial microsurgery
Dennis R. Buis, C. Rob Buis, Ricardo E. Feller, Ellen S. Mandl, Saskia M. Peerdeman
BackgroundIntracranial microsurgical procedures often take place in a deep location, with a limited access space, necessitating the use of long knee-bend instruments and limiting the degree of movement. We devised an easily accessible model that allows the neurosurgical trainee to gain familiarity with intracranial microsurgical techniques.
